@Charles Freeman. Thank u Charles! I am familiar with ur writing, and do watch it closely (criticism is always welcome!), since I don’t think that it is a painting. Also, I agree with the Ian Wilson theory. Now, on some more details (if there are interested parties), when it comes to the Eastern rite involving the epitaphios and icons “not made by a human hand”, I recommend the works of one Aleksey Lidov, https://moscowstate.academia.edu/AlexeiLidov
And, recommend the investigation of the further Mandylion type developments when it comes to the frescoepaintings. I am doing that for some time now. Example from Serbia, 1234. http://i57.tinypic.com/17saqw.jpg
Cheers!
